headline: Nasdaq Could Mark Biggest Comeback Since April. Wall Street Is Buying the Dip in Nvidia and Other AI Stocks.
summary: The Nasdaq Composite clawed back to positive territory as a handful of key AI stocks like Nvidia rallied off their lows.  The S&P 500 was down 0.2%, though only 147 stocks in the index were in positive territory.  Nvidia turned positive and was up 0.5% in recent trading.

headline: Siemens Energy Closes The Book On 2025 Amid 'Unprecedented Demand' For Gas Turbines
summary: Siemens Energy reported fiscal fourth-quarter earnings and revenue early Friday, closing the book on fiscal 2025 and on a year marked by strong demand for gas turbines amid expected increases in the need for electricity and the AI data center boom.  Siemens Energy also reported a net profit of 236 million euros ($274.6 million) compared with a loss of 254 million euros a year ago.  Siemens Energy added that will look to achieve compound annual revenue growth in the low-teens percentage range through 2028.
